data.title: Music Lessons in Pittsburgh
data.meta_description: Learn music the fun way at Sunburst School of Music in Pittsburgh! Our in-person and online lesson offerings include guitar, piano, voice, bass, drums, ukulele, and music production as well as a variety of group programs, classes, and camps.
data.text:
Explore the world of music with your child in our Music Together® classes! These fun-filled, 45-minute sessions for kids aged 0–5 are all about singing, dancing, and building musical skills. The classes offer a chance to bond with your child and ignite a lifelong passion for music.

To learn more about Music Together classes for you and your child, check out our Mixed-Age and Rhythm Kids® classes.

Our school features an in-house stage for open-mic nights, concerts, and seasonal student recitals. We also organize performance opportunities at local venues like Mr. Smalls Theatre, The Hard Rock Café, and more! We believe all students should have access to a supportive space where they can practice their performing and show off their skills!

Take your artistry to the next level with the wide-range of Sunburst performance opportunities!

We offer lessons:

11AM to 9PM Monday - Thursday

11AM to 7PM Fridays

9AM to 5PM Saturdays & Sundays.

Our plans are month to month and we have a flexible rescheduling policy to help keep our students on track. Our friendly and knowledgeable office staff is here to help help every step of the way . We also offer online music lessons via Zoom for those looking to learn an instrument from home!
